source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/skillet-chilaquiles-552e85bb6ced6e9b3c8b4569
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping the white and
green parts separate. Halve the @tomato{1}, remove and discard the seeds and white
core, then finely dice. Thinly slice the @radishes{3}. Coarsely chop the
@cilantro{1%bunch}. Halve the @lime{1}. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%can}.

Heat @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the scallion whites
and cook for ~{30%seconds}. Add the black beans, chopped tomato, and 1 teaspoon
abodo sauce from the @chipotles in adobo{1%can} (more if you like the heat!).
Cook for ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and set aside.

In the same pan, mound the @tortilla chips{3%ounces}. Top with the black bean
mixture and sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Bake for ~{5-10%minutes},
until cheese has melted.

Meanwhile, toss the radishes and half the cilantro with the juice of half a lime.
Season with salt and pepper.

> This would be a great time to fry up two egg to top the chilaquiles with, if
> desired!

Remove the pan from the oven and top with the radish and cilantro salad. Top
with the scallion greens, remaining cilantro, a dollop of @sour cream{2%tbsp},
and a squeeze of lime juice.

> If you're a serious heat-seeker, add more adobo sauce or even some chopped
> chipotle pepper on top!